================================================================================
CHANGES IMPLEMENTED
================================================================================

1. Added SCALE_DOWN_THRESHOLD = 50% configuration
2. Created deprovision_gcp_instance() function
   - Deletes GCP instance via gcloud
   - Removes firewall rules
   - Returns to local VM monitoring

3. Refactored main() loop:
   - Continuous monitoring (while True, not while not scaled)
   - Tracks both high_load_count and low_load_count
   - Shows status: [LOCAL] or [SCALED]
   - Scale up: CPU/Mem > 75% for 4 checks
   - Scale down: CPU/Mem < 50% for 4 checks
   
4. Removed all emojis from output
5. Fixed syntax warning (dollar sign escape)

================================================================================
NEW MONITORING OUTPUT FORMAT
================================================================================

Before scaling:
  [LOCAL] [22:00:00] CPU: 5.0% | Memory: 35.0%

High load detected:
  [LOCAL] [22:01:00] CPU: 100.0% | Memory: 35.0% [HIGH] Count: 1/4
  [LOCAL] [22:01:30] CPU: 100.0% | Memory: 35.0% [HIGH] Count: 2/4
  ...
  [LOCAL] [22:02:30] CPU: 100.0% | Memory: 35.0% [HIGH] Count: 4/4
  
  Sustained high load detected! Scaling up...

After scaling up:
  [SCALED] [22:05:00] CPU: 95.0% | Memory: 36.0%

Low load detected:
  [SCALED] [22:08:00] CPU: 10.0% | Memory: 35.0% [LOW] Count: 1/4
  [SCALED] [22:08:30] CPU: 5.0% | Memory: 35.0% [LOW] Count: 2/4
  ...
  [SCALED] [22:09:30] CPU: 3.0% | Memory: 34.0% [LOW] Count: 4/4
  
  Sustained low load detected! Scaling down...

Back to local:
  [LOCAL] [22:10:00] CPU: 2.0% | Memory: 34.0%

